  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Maria Weston Chapman congratulates Elizabeth Pease Nichol on the formation of the British India Society. The American abolitionists are enthusiastic about its objectives. Mr. &amp; Mrs. Wendell Phillips &quot;write to me of the great satisfaction they have had in knowing you.&quot; J. Scoble has been lecturing on West Indian emancipation. Some abolitionists &quot;are labouring to extinguish the religious opinions of their brethren on other subjects, instead of co-operating with them against the common enemy.&quot; Chapman explained the reason for the religious differences among abolitionists to an audience in Lynn. She sends the pamphlet, Right and Wrong in Massachusetts.</subfield>
